               <history>
                  <origin>
                    <origDate notBefore="1841" notAfter="1867">1841-67.</origDate>
                    The concluding supplication of <ref target="#p1_i2"/> mentions the metropolitan
                    <persName ref="PRS8388SalamaI">ʾabuna Salāmā III</persName>, the sponsors <persName ref="PRS13127TasfaMaryam">Tasfā Māryām</persName> and
                    <persName ref="PRS13128GadlaGiyorgis">Gadla Giyorgis</persName> who acquired the manuscript for <placeName ref="LOC2320DabraM">the church of Dabra
                    Māʿḍo Yoḥannǝs</placeName>.
                    Other supplication formulas mention, apart from <persName ref="PRS13127TasfaMaryam">Tasfā Māryām</persName> (<locus target="#4ra #6ra #8ra #9vb #13rb
                    #18rb"/>) and <persName ref="PRS13128GadlaGiyorgis">Gadla Giyorgis</persName> (<locus target="#4rb #11rb #17va"/>), also Walatta Mikāʾel (<locus target="#13va"/>),
                  and Nǝgǝśta Māryām (<locus target="#4vb"/>, poorly visible).
                  </origin>
               </history>
