                               <locus from="21ra" to="48rb"/>
                               <seg type="script">First half of the nineteenth century raqiq script.</seg>
                               <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                                <seg type="rubrication">Divine names (the name of
                                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>); names of the donors; name of the scribe; elements
                                of the numerals and punctuation signs. Rubrication has been
                                executed in the same hand, after the copying of the main text.</seg>
                                <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Zadǝngǝl</persName>, active at least in <date>1822-28</date> as attested in
                                Ms. <ref type="mss" corresp="ESagq002">ˁAddi Qolqʷāl Giyorgis 2</ref>, and probably also in a later period.
                              <desc>Not very careful, somewhat irregular, hasty; by a mediocre scribe.
