                    <history>
                       <origin>
                          <ref target="#p2">Unit 2</ref> can be dated to the
                          <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1849">first half of the nineteenth century.</origDate>
                          The text was copied by the scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName>.
                          The supplication formulas
                          mention <persName ref="PRS13129TasfaHeywat">Tasfā Ḥǝywat</persName> (<ref target="#21r #25r #34r #36v #40v #42v #44r #46v"/>),
                          <persName ref="PRS13131WalattaMikael">Walatta Mikāʾel</persName> (<ref target="#29r #38v #45r"/>), <persName ref="PRS13130SegeMikael">Ṣǝge Mikāʾel</persName> (<ref target="#47v #46r #48r"/>) (different from
                          the sponsors of <ref target="#p1">Unit 1</ref>).
                          <ref target="#p2">Unit 2</ref> could be possibly a circulation unit before it was
                          included into the binding of <ref target="#p1"/>.
                          </origin>
                    </history>
